          <p> Please follow these steps in completing your VISA application.
       </p>
            <h5>Step 1: Making a plan</h5>
            <p>Determine where you will have your VISA processed. You have different options:</p>
    
        <ol>
            <li>In person: submit your application in person to the Visa Application Centers in Ottawa, Montreal and Toronto.
                <ol type="a"><li>If you are outside of Canada, you can follow the same steps and apply in person to the Russian Embassy of your host city (http://www.russianconsulates.com/)</li></ol>
            </li>
            <li>Local representative: ask a local representative (friend, relative, colleague, COC staff, etc.) to submit the application for you. 
                <ol type="a">
                    <li>You must have an authorization letter that confirms that your give your local representative permission to submit your application for you.</li>
                    <li><a href="/pdf/coc-third_party_authorization_letter_example.docx" target="_blank">Click here</a> for an example of an authorization letter.</li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li>Mail: applications can be mailed to the Visa Application Center but should be done at least 30 days prior to your departure. No rush service is available by mail.</li>
        </ol>
    
    
        <h5>Step 2: tourist voucher / confirmation from a Russian HOST</h5>
        <ul>
            <li>Prior to submitting your VISA application to the Visa Application Centers, you must obtain a “tourist voucher” and “confirmation” from a Russian hosting travel agency or hotel registered with the Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs which confirms your trip to Russia. The voucher must be signed by an authorized person and carry the official seal of the Russian travel company with its reference number. Please <a href="#tourist_voucher" data-toggle="modal" >click here</a> for an example.
            </li>
            <li>You will need to ask for a voucher through your hotel. In order to obtain the voucher, you will need to make sure your passport is valid for 6 months after your departure date from Russia, has 2 completely blank pages face-to-face (not including pages 1-5), should be signed on page 3 and should be in good condition. 
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>Please note that it can take up to a minimum of 2 weeks to obtain a voucher or confirmation from any organization. Once you receive your voucher or confirmation, you will be given a reference number which must accompany your VISA application. </p>
    
        <h5>Step 3: Application Form</h5>
        <p>The process to apply for your VISA is the same no matter what region you currently reside in. 
            </p>
        <p>Online application link: <a href="https://visa.kdmid.ru/PetitionChoice.aspx">https://visa.kdmid.ru/PetitionChoice.aspx</a> </p>
    
        A few things to consider when completing your application form:
        <ul>
            <li>The form must be printed on both sides of a single piece of paper.
                <ul>
                    <li>NOTE: do not use the printing instructions used on the website. When printing, ensure the top and bottom of the pages are not cut off. They will not accept your form if it is cut off.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Any corrections or whiteout on the forms will not be accepted.</li>
            <li>Sign and date the application with a black ink.</li>
        </ul>
        <h5>Step 4: Photo</h5>
        In order to complete your application documents, you must obtain a VISA photo that meets the following specifications and is glued (not stapled) in the appropriate spot on your VISA Application Form:
        <ul>
            <li>The frame size must be 35 mm x 45 mm</li>
            <li>Photo must be taken in the last 6 months prior to application</li>
            <li>Photo must be clear and taken against a plain white or light background</li>
            <li>Sunglasses are not acceptable</li>
            <li>The photo must show the full front view of the head, with the face in the middle of the photo, and include the top of the shoulders</li>
            <li>You must have a neutral expression, neither frowning nor smiling, and with your mouth closed </li>
     	</ul>
        <h5>Step 5: Sending it In</h5>
        <p>
            Once you have completed all the forms and gathered all the documentation needed to apply for your VISA, please either drop it off in person or by someone you know at the Ottawa, Toronto or Montreal Visa Application Centers. 
        </p>
        <p>
            In order to apply, you will need your passport, a photocopy of the ID page of your passport, your printed application, a visa photo (see step 4), your tourist voucher (with the reference number),a money order, bank draft, certified cheque payable to INVISA LOGISTIC SERVICES CANADA LTD or cash.
        </p>
        Processing Time
        <p>
            Please note that VISA applications can take up to approximately 20 days to process (30 days if your application is mailed in) and a rush application is approximately 3 days. Please give yourself sufficient time to allow you to receive your passport prior to your departure for Sochi.
        </p>
        <p>
            Although it has been noted that some consulates are able to provide same day VISA applications if you apply in person and arrive when the office opens (see business hours below), the normal turn around for in person applications is between 3 and 5 days. Please consult with your respective consulate as this may vary based on the time of year and number of applications received any given week.
        </p>
        <p>
            More information on the Russian Visa Application process can be found here: <a href="http://www.canada-ils.com/main.php?id=index&lang=en">http://www.canada-ils.com/main.php?id=index&lang=en</a>
        </p>
        <h5>Cost of Applying for a VISA</h5>
        <p>
            Please note they do not accept credit cards or company / personal cheques. Consular and ILS visa processing fees are non-refundable and included in the total price. ILS fee remains the same regardless of your visa type and processing time.
        </p>
